# .secretsignore
# 
# This file contains patterns for strings that should be allowed in the production build
# even if they match secret detection patterns.
#
# Format:
#   - Lines starting with # are comments
#   - Empty lines are ignored
#   - Exact matches: just write the string
#   - Glob patterns: use * for wildcards (e.g., test-*-key)
#   - Regex patterns: enclose in / (e.g., /pattern/i)
#
# Examples:
#   VITE_PUBLIC_API_KEY          # Exact match
#   test-*-key                   # Glob pattern (matches test-api-key, test-secret-key, etc.)
#   /^demo-[a-z]+-token$/        # Regex pattern

# ============================================================================
# Public Environment Variables
# ============================================================================
# VITE_ prefixed variables are public by design and bundled into the app
VITE_API_URL
VITE_APP_NAME
VITE_PUBLIC_KEY

# ============================================================================
